==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rasure
<hw>Ra"sure</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"zh⟦usl⟧r; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>rasura</ets>, fr. <ets>radere</ets>, <ets>rasum</ets>, to
scrape, to shave. See <er>Rase</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of rasing, scraping, or erasing; erasure;
obliteration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mark by which a letter, word, or any part of a
writing or print, is erased, effaced, or obliterated; an erasure.</def>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rat</ent>⟦br⟧
